          "sequence": 43,
          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I've completed the impact analysis for `ModelAdmin.get_list_filter()`. Here's a summary of my findings:\n\n## Impact Analysis Summary\n\nI found **5 files** in the Django repository that reference `get_list_filter`:\n\n### 1. **Main Definition & Callers**\n- **`django/contrib/admin/options.py`** - Contains the definition of `get_list_filter()` (line 1110) and its callers:\n  - Line 498: Called in a method that validates lookups\n  - Line 863: Called when creating a ChangeList instance\n\n### 2. **Test Overrides**\n- **`tests/admin_changelist/admin.py`** (line 181-186) - `DynamicListFilterChildAdmin` class overrides `get_list_filter()` to dynamically filter based on user\n- **`tests/modeladmin/tests.py`** (line 245-248) - `ConcertAdmin` class in test overrides `get_list_filter()` to add dynamic filters\n\n### 3. **Documentation**\n- **`docs/ref/contrib/admin/index.txt`** - Contains documentation of the method at line 1605-1611, with an additional reference at line 1911\n- **`docs/releases/1.5.txt`** - References the method in release notes (line 349)\n\n## Results\nThe findings have been written to `/workspace/submission.json` as a JSON array containing all 5 affected file paths relative to the repository root.\n\nThe submission includes:\n- \u2705 The original definition\n- \u2705 All overrides (2 test overrides found)\n- \u2705 All callers (2 calls within the main definition file)\n- \u2705 Documentation references (2 documentation files)",
